claim.claim-text:
A rotorcraft, comprising:
a body;
a power train coupled to the body and comprising a power source and a drive shaft coupled to the power source;
a hub coupled to the drive shaft;
a rotor blade coupled to the hub;
a swashplate positioned about the drive shaft;
a pitch link coupled between the swashplate and the hub corresponding to the rotor blade;
a bearing coupled between either the pitch link and the swashplate or the pitch link and the hub, the bearing comprising:
an outer housing having a first opening therethrough;
an elastomeric bearing adjacent the housing inside the first opening and having a second opening therethrough;
an inner housing adjacent the elastomeric bearing inside the second opening and having a third opening therethrough, the inner housing comprising a first inner surface and a second inner surface defining the third opening, the second inner surface oriented at a reflex angle relative to the first inner surface such that an interior diameter of the third opening is smaller than an exterior diameter of the third opening;
a first member adjacent the first inner surface inside the third opening having a fourth opening therethrough;
a first bearing surface in contact with the first inner surface and the first member and separating the first inner surface from the first member;
a second member adjacent the second inner surface inside the third opening having a fifth opening therethrough coaxial with the fourth opening; and
a second bearing surface in contact with the second inner surface and the second member and separating the second inner surface from the second member.

The rotorcraft of claim 1, further comprising a second bearing coupled to the pitch link opposite the first bearing, the second bearing comprising:
an outer housing having a first opening therethrough;
an elastomeric bearing adjacent the housing inside the first opening and having a second opening therethrough;
an inner housing adjacent the elastomeric bearing inside the second opening and having a third opening therethrough, the inner housing comprising a first inner surface and a second inner surface defining the third opening, the second inner surface oriented at a reflex angle relative to the first inner surface such that an interior diameter of the third opening is smaller than an exterior diameter of the third opening;
a first member adjacent the first inner surface inside the third opening having a fourth opening therethrough;
a first bearing surface in contact with the first inner surface and the first member and separating the first inner surface from the first member;
a second member adjacent the second inner surface inside the third opening having a fifth opening therethrough coaxial with the fourth opening; and
a second bearing surface in contact with the second inner surface and the second member and separating the second inner surface from the second member.

A bearing, comprising:
an outer housing having a first opening therethrough;
an elastomeric bearing adjacent the housing inside the first opening and having a second opening therethrough;
an inner housing adjacent the elastomeric bearing inside the second opening and having a third opening therethrough, the inner housing comprising a first inner surface and a second inner surface defining the third opening, the second inner surface oriented at a reflex angle relative to the first inner surface such that an interior diameter of the third opening is smaller than an exterior diameter of the third opening;
a first member adjacent the first inner surface inside the third opening having a fourth opening therethrough;
a first bearing surface in contact with the first inner surface and the first member and separating the first inner surface from the first member;
a second member adjacent the second inner surface inside the third opening having a fifth opening therethrough coaxial with the fourth opening; and
a second bearing surface in contact with the second inner surface and the second member and separating the second inner surface from the second member.

A method for manufacturing a bearing, comprising:
providing an outer housing having a first opening therethrough;
inserting an elastomeric bearing adjacent the housing inside the first opening, the elastomeric bearing having a second opening therethrough;
inserting an inner housing adjacent the elastomeric bearing inside the second opening, the inner housing having a third opening therethrough, the inner housing comprising a first inner surface and a second inner surface defining the third opening, the second inner surface oriented at a reflex angle relative to the first inner surface such that an interior diameter of the third opening is smaller than an exterior diameter of the third opening;
inserting a first member adjacent the first inner surface inside the third opening, the first member having a fourth opening therethrough, wherein a first bearing surface is in contact with the first inner surface and the first member and separates the first inner surface from the first member; and
inserting a second member adjacent the second inner surface inside the third opening, the second member having a fifth opening therethrough coaxial with the fourth opening, wherein a second bearing surface is in contact with the second inner surface and the second member and separates the second inner surface from the second member, and optionally or preferably
wherein the first bearing surface is a fluorocarbon bearing.

1. A bearing (200), comprising:
an outer housing (210) having a first opening therethrough; and
characterized by an elastomeric bearing (220) adjacent the housing inside the first opening and having a second opening therethrough;
an inner housing (230) adjacent the elastomeric bearing inside the second opening and having a third opening therethrough, the inner housing comprising a first inner surface (230a) and a second inner surface (230b) defining the third opening, the second inner surface (230b) oriented at a reflex angle (α) relative to the first inner surface (230a) such that an interior diameter of the third opening (d1) is smaller than an exterior diameter of the third opening (d2);
a first member (240a) adjacent the first inner surface (230a) inside the third opening having a fourth opening therethrough;
a first bearing surface (250a) in contact with the first inner surface (230a) and the first member (240a) and separating the first inner surface from the first member;
a second member (240b) adjacent the second inner surface (230b) inside the third opening having a fifth opening therethrough coaxial with the fourth opening; and
a second bearing surface (250b) in contact with the second inner surface (230b) and the second member (240b) and separating the second inner surface from the second member

2. A rotorcraft (100), comprising:
a body (130);
a power train (112) coupled to the body and comprising a power source (112a) and a drive shaft (112b) coupled to the power source;
a hub (114) coupled to the drive shaft (112b);
a rotor blade (120) coupled to the hub (114);
a swashplate (116) positioned about the drive shaft (112b);
a pitch link (118) coupled between the swashplate (116) and the hub (114) corresponding to the rotor blade; and
a bearing as claimed in claim 1 coupled between either the pitch link (118) and the swashplate (116) or the pitch link (118) and the hub (114).

13. A method for manufacturing a bearing (200), comprising:
providing an outer housing (210) having a first opening therethrough;
inserting an elastomeric bearing (220) adjacent the housing inside the first opening, the elastomeric bearing having a second opening therethrough;
inserting an inner housing (230) adjacent the elastomeric bearing inside the second opening, the inner housing having a third opening therethrough, the inner housing comprising a first inner surface (230a) and a second inner surface (230b) defining the third opening, the second inner surface oriented at a reflex angle (α) relative to the first inner surface such that an interior diameter of the third opening is smaller than an exterior diameter of the third opening;
inserting a first member (240a) adjacent the first inner surface (230a) inside the third opening, the first member having a fourth opening therethrough, wherein a first bearing surface (250a) is in contact with the first inner surface and the first member and separates the first inner surface from the first member; and
inserting a second member (240b) adjacent the second inner surface (230b) inside the third opening, the second member having a fifth opening therethrough coaxial with the fourth opening, wherein a second bearing surface (250b) is in contact with the second inner surface and the second member and separates the second inner surface from the second member, and optionally or preferably
wherein the first bearing surface is a fluorocarbon bearing.
